<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Israel </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official's Remarks Clarified </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official's Remarks Clarified </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2004131694 Tel Aviv MA'ARIV in Hebrew 20 Apr 94 p 6 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> TA2004131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv MA'ARIV </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hemi Shalev] </F>
  [Text] Following MA'ARIV's 18 April report on Assistant 
Foreign Ministry Director General Eytan Bentzur's assessments 
regarding of the functioning of the U.S. Administration, the 
foreign minister's bureau sought to clarify that Foreign 
Minister Shim'on Peres "highly appreciates the efforts of the 
U.S. secretary of state and the American peace team, who have 
greatly contributed to the peace process, and thanks the Clinton 
Administration in general for the warm attitude it has shown 
Israel." 
  The bureau's statement asserted that the Foreign Ministry 
"was not party to the opinions of the senior official with 
regard to the policies of the Administration and the peace team 
and these opinions are merely his own personal views." 

</TEXT>

