<H3> <TI>   Major General Appointed To Head New Central Command </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Major General Appointed To Head New Central Command </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1304101994 Jerusalem THE JERUSALEM POST in English 13 Apr 
94 p 1 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> TA1304101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem THE JERUSALEM POST </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alon Pinkas] </F>
  [Text] Maj. Gen. Ilan Biran, 48, will be the new OC 
Central Command as of Sunday. 
  Prime Minister and Defense Minister Yitzhaq Rabin approved 
Chief of General Staff Lt.-Gen. Ehud Baraq's recommendation to 
appoint Biran to the post. 
  Biran will replace Acting OC Central Command Maj-Gen. Dani 
Yatom, who temporarily took over after the death of Maj.-Gen. 
Nehemya Tamari in a helicopter crash last January. Yatom will 
return to his post as military secretary to Rabin. 
  Born in 1946 in Qiryat Hayim, Biran was drafted in 1964 and 
has spent most of his military career in the Golani Brigade. In 
the Yom Kippur War, Biran was a battalion commander. He later 
served as commander of the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] central 
offices school and commander of an armored division. In 1987 he 
was appointed chief of operations in the General Staff. 
  Biran was promoted to major-general in 1989, together with 
his appointment to head the Logistics Branch. 
  Biran holds a bachelor's degree in economics and business 
administration from Bar-Ilan University. He is also a graduate 
of the US Marine Corps Command and Staff College at Quantico, 
Virginia. In 1992-93, Biran was on academic leave at the 
Georgetown University School of Foreign Service. Biran is 
married and father of three daughters and a son. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

