<H3> <TI>   Opposition Figure Visits Israel, Holds Talks With Rabin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Figure Visits Israel, Holds Talks With Rabin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2104204194 Amman AKHBAR AL-USBU' in Arabic 21 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2104204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHBAR AL-USBU' </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Occupied Jerusalem -- Jawad Hashim, Iraqi opposition 
figure and former minister, has paid a secret visit to Israel 
and met with Yitzhaq Rabin, Israeli prime minister and minister 
of defense. He also met with many Israeli officials, including 
Shim'on Peres, the foreign minister, and Moshe Shahal, minister 
of police and energy. Moreover, Hashim met with several members 
of the Labor and Likud parties in the Knesset. 
  It is noteworthy that this visit by Jawad Hashim, who has 
been to Israel more than once during the past few years, lasted 
for several days last week. 
  Minister Hashim has lived in Europe since the Gulf crisis. 

</TEXT>

