<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paper Comments on Recent Downing of U.S. Helicopters </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper Comments on Recent Downing of U.S. Helicopters </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2104114494 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0850 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2104114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 21 Apr (INA)--The newspaper AL-QADISIYAH 
has said that the downing of two U.S. helicopters by U.S. 
aircraft over northern Iraq has revealed the broad rejection of 
the U.S. policies of hegemony, violence, and aggression. 
  In an article today entitled "The Downing of the U.S. 
Helicopters Is First Drops of Rain," the paper adds: Numerous 
facts will certainly be revealed about similar U.S. crimes which 
used to be kept secret or forgotten, now that, after the downing 
of the two U.S. helicopters, the White House can no longer 
conceal these cheap and lowly adventures after they have been 
exposed to the whole world. 
  AL-QADISIYAH adds: Such mistakes will continue to be made 
without any justification apart from the U.S. grudge against 
peoples and the desire to control and dominate them. No wonder, 
therefore, that this topic has drawn the attention of the world 
media. The paper continues: Everyone is aware of the tragedies 
of wars and military interventions led by the United States in 
the world. Everyone recalls, in particular, the U.S. crimes in 
Vietnam, Panama, Nicaragua, Korea, and Iraq as well as the 
distress caused to both the American people and the world as a 
result of the reckless U.S. policy. 
  The paper wonders how the American people feel regarding the 
many U.S. soldiers who died in the U.S. wars, and who are left 
with only memories. The paper concludes that history will 
uncover the folded pages even if they are concealed by the dust 
of years or the smoke of intelligence services and those 
revolving in their orbit. 

</TEXT>

