<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Basindwa Denies Diplomatic `Reshuffle' Aimed at YSP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Basindwa Denies Diplomatic `Reshuffle' Aimed at YSP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2104091494 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 20 Apr 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PM2104091494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "In Message From Yemeni Foreign </F>
Ministry to AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT, Sanaa Denies Bias Against 
Socialist Party Diplomats"] 
  [Excerpt] London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Yemeni Foreign 
Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah has denied a reshuffle of 
staff -- in particular southern Yemeni diplomats and those who 
have close links with the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP]. 
  He expressed his regret that "some people should exploit the 
crisis Yemen is experiencing to distort facts and level false 
accusations at others." 
  In a statement AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT received from a Yemeni 
Foreign Ministry official, Basindwah said that "with regard to 
the ministry's delay in sending financial allowances to the 
embassies, this delay is not limited to certain embassies. It 
affects all embassies." 
  This came as a reply to accusations made by some Yemeni 
sources regarding a diplomatic reshuffle aimed at recalling to 
Yemen YSP diplomats or those close to the YSP, and the Foreign 
Ministry's deliberate delay in sending financial allowances to 
the embassies where they work. 
  The foreign minister attributed the delay in sending these 
allowances to "the Central Bank's inability to secure the sums 
decided in hard currency on the specified dates." [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

