<H3> <TI>   Peres, 'Arafat Continue Talks in Bucharest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres, 'Arafat Continue Talks in Bucharest </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Peres, 'Arafat Hold News Conference </H4>

<F P=102> TA2104180194 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2104180194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report on joint news conference by Foreign Minister Shim'on </F>
Peres and PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat in Bucharest on 21 April -- 
recorded] 
  [Text] A joint news conference by Foreign Minister Shim'on 
Peres and PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat ended in Bucharest a short 
while ago. The two summed up with satisfaction 24 hours of 
intensive discussions. The following is an excerpt of the news 
conference: 
  [Begin recording] ['Arafat, in English] We are all doing 
our best to find a solution for this conflict. I don't want to 
say conflict, no, but it's a conflict between brothers. I am 
sure of that, especially with his excellency, Mr. Peres, with 
his goodwill, we can push forward the peace process. 
  [Peres] So I think the unhappiness of Yugoslavia is 
different from the unhappiness in the Middle East, and 
furthermore, in Yugoslavia you have an aggressor and you have a 
victim. In the case of the Middle East you have two negotiators 
who are trying to put an end to the conflict. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

