<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres, 'Arafat Continue Talks in Bucharest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres, 'Arafat Continue Talks in Bucharest </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Accord Reached on 3 Committees </H4>

<F P=102> TA2104184794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1800 GMT 21 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2104184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In their talks in Bucharest today Foreign Minister 
Shim'on Peres and PLO leader, Yasir 'Arafat, agreed to establish 
and man three committees which will operate during the overlap 
period between the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] withdrawal and 
the establishment of autonomy: a committee on routine security, 
a committee on joint patrols, and a committee on the transfer of 
administration powers. 
  Our correspondent Gid'on Kouts reports that Peres and 
'Arafat 
will meet again in an hour for the fourth time. They will then 
decide whether they will meet in Cairo next weekend. The two 
sides apparently set the first week of May as a target date for 
the signing of the agreement. 
  In a speech before the economic forum in Bucharest Minister 
Peres said that the peace process is irreversible. In his 
speech, 'Arafat condemned acts of violence by both sides, saying 
the PLO is committed to democracy and a market economy. He 
again warned that if an agreement is not achieved, balkanization 
of the Middle East is expected. 
  An agreement was achieved in the Paris economic talks 
between 
Israel and the PLO on free tourism traffic between Israel and 
the autonomy. At the same time, our correspondent Yo'av Tocker 
notes that the dispute on customs issues remains. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

