<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Another Round of Palestinian Autonomy Talks Ends </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Another Round of Palestinian Autonomy Talks Ends </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Talks To Resume 24 Apr </H4>

<F P=102> NC2104123294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1150 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2104123294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 21 Apr (MENA)--The Palestinian and Israeli 
negotiators ended a round of negotiations in Cairo on the 
implementation of the Gaza-Jericho agreement with a meeting by 
the Civilian Affairs Committee this morning. 
  Dr. Nabil Sha'th, adviser to Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat and head of the Palestinian negotiating delegation, said 
the negotiations with the Israelis will resumed on 24 April to 
discuss the remaining outstanding issues. He said that only 
five clauses remain to be discussed in the general agreement 
between the two sides. 
  Sha'th explained that the first air route to be established 
after an international airport is established in Gaza will be 
between Gaza and Cairo. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

