<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Another Round of Palestinian Autonomy Talks Ends </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Another Round of Palestinian Autonomy Talks Ends </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Israeli Delegation Leaves Cairo </H4>

<F P=102> NC2104141394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1332 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2104141394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 21 Apr (MENA)--The Israeli delegation 
participating in the Israeli-Palestinian peace talks led by 
Deputy Chief of Staff Amnon Shahaq left Cairo this afternoon 
after a visit of several days and the end of a round of talks 
with the Palestinian delegation. 
  In a statement made before his departure, Shahaq said that 
the talks will resume in Cairo on Sunday to follow up on the 
previous rounds. He said that progress was made on the civilian 
and legal issues, noting that the talks were held in a positive 
atmosphere. 

</TEXT>

