<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Lists Conditions for `Truce' With Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Lists Conditions for `Truce' With Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2104135794 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1200 GMT 21 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2104135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Damascus, the Hamas Movement has proposed a truce 
with Israel to find a way out of the Palestinian crisis. In a 
statement issued in Damascus, Hamas Political Bureau chief Musa 
Abu-Marzuq said his proposal is based on the following 
principles: Comprehensive Israeli withdrawal from the West Bank, 
the Gaza Strip, and occupied Jerusalem, and the dismantling of 
all settlements in the occupied territories and the evacuation 
of the settlers. 
  Abu-Marzuq emphasized the need to hold free and fair general 
elections among the Palestinian people in order to elect their 
leadership and representatives. He promised the Hamas Movement 
will respect the views of the majority. 

</TEXT>

