<H3> <TI>   Sha'th on Western Failure To Fulfill Aid Pledges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th on Western Failure To Fulfill Aid Pledges </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2204100594 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0800 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2204100594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cairo, 22 Apr (INA)--Nabil Sha'th, the 
Palestinian president's adviser, has criticized the evasion by 
the U.S. Administration and other Western countries of their 
pledges to extend needed financial aid to the Palestinian 
self-rule area in Gaza and Jericho. 
  Sha'th told the IRAQI NEWS AGENCY correspondent in Cairo 
yesterday that the United States and other Western countries 
halted the extension of the pledged financial aid to the 
Palestinian side. Expressing regret over this deceitful retreat, 
he said that reality has shown that these pledges were merely 
promises. 
  The Palestinian official asserted that, for its part, the 
Zionist entity has also tried to evade its pledges in the 
Washington agreement on Palestinian self-rule in Jericho and 
Gaza. [passage omitted] 

