<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy to UN Calls For Measures in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Envoy to UN Calls For Measures in Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2204070794 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0500 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2204070794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Egypt has warned that the UN could lose its 
credibility in the face of the deteriorating situation in 
Gorazde. Dr. Nabil al-'Arabi, Egypt's permanent delegate to the 
UN, said in a speech to the Security Council last night that the 
UN has two alternatives. Either to adopt the collective security 
measures stipulated under the UN Charter to end the existing 
aggression against Bosnia-Herzegovina and force the aggressors 
to withdraw or lift the military embargo imposed on Bosnia. 
  Dr. al-'Arabi noted that the Egyptian delegation had 
repeatedly cautioned the Security Council against the 
consequences of failure to adopt decisive measures to ensure a 
firm and decisive remedy of the deteriorating situation in 
Bosnia. He called on the Security Council members to adopt the 
immediate and necessary measures to put an end to this tragedy, 
which cannot be tolerated. Chief among these measures are for 
the NATO to undertake the immediate military actions needed to 
lift the siege of Gorazde, force the Serbs to withdraw from the 
town, back the Bosnia-Herzegovina Government in its legitimate 
right to self-defense, and lift the military embargo imposed on 
it, he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

