<H3> <TI>   Security Services Investigating Leaks to al-Jihad Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Services Investigating Leaks to al-Jihad Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2104162794 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 18 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2104162794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Najwa 'Abd-al-'Aziz] </F>
  [Text] Security authorities and some diplomatic quarters 
are conducting extensive investigations into how the names, 
posts, and movements of some foreign diplomats were leaked to 
the extremist al-Jihad organization members who were recently 
arrested. Interpol is also participating in these 
investigations. 
  The security authorities seized a list of the diplomats 
targeted for assassination along with the members of the 
extremist group, which was led by 'Adil 'Awad, who was killed in 
the al-Munib battle on 14 April. 
  The extremists confessed to receiving instructions from 
their 
leadership abroad to assassinate the foreign diplomats, 
especially Americans and Israelis. 
  The security authorities also discovered the underground 
"cells," which the organization's members had prepared in 
al-Qattamiyah and Bilbays to kidnap the diplomats and detain 
them there. 
  An investigation is underway on how the detainees identified 
the persons mentioned in the assassination list, which was 
seized in one of the organization's hideouts. The investigation 
authorities held face-to-face confrontations with the eight 
defendants. 

</TEXT>

