<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 21 Apr (MENA)--Ten convicts of various 
nationalities--four Sudanese, two Bangladeshis, one Somali, one 
Indian, one Tanzanian, and one Kenyan--charged with drug 
trafficking and smuggling into Egypt were executed today. 
  The Court of Cassation upheld the verdicts to execute these 
convicts in February and President Husni Mubarak endorsed them. 
Justice Minister Counselor Faruq Sayf-al-Nasr stated that this 
is the first time so many convicts in drug trafficking have been 
executed at one time. 

