<F P=102>   TA2204052294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 22 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2204052294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Activists working on behalf of keeping the Golan 
Heights under Israeli control say they are launching a giant 
campaign following Prime Minister Rabin's statement yesterday 
that he would be willing to dismantle settlements on the Golan 
Heights in exchange for peace with Syria. On the fallout from 
the preime minister's statement, David Ze'ev: 
  [Begin Ze'ev recording] Golan Heights activists from around 
the country are said to be ready to launch what is being 
described as a giant demonstration and information campaign. 
Over 100 branches of the Golan movement are preparing for 
intensive activity during the coming weeks, following the prime 
minister's statement yesterday on dismantling Golan settlements. 
  U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher has tried to 
lower 
expectations for his visit to the Middle East, which he 
announced will start Sunday, but Israel's Deputy Foreign 
Minister Yosi Beilin says the prime minister's statement 
yesterday was one of a series by Israeli officials recently that 
contribute to the possibility of changing the very slow pace of 
negotiations with Syria, as he put it, to something which is 
more intensive than that. [passage omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

