<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gaza Closure Eased After IDF-Fatah Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2104194294 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2104194294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The closure on the territories has been eased. 
Some 1,000 Gaza residents were today allowed to enter the Green 
Line boundaries through the Erez roadblock. Our correspondent 
Shlomi Eldar reports that entry permits were granted not only to 
laborers but also to family members of Palestinians who are 
detained in Qezi'ot, as per an agreement reached in negotiations 
between Fatah and the IDF [Israel Defense Forces]. The IDF 
commander in the Gaza Strip also permitted PLO people to enter 
Israel. They had been allowed free passage in the past, but 
their exit from the Strip was restricted after the imposition of 
the closure. 

