<H3> <TI>   Minister Explains al-Majali's Cancellation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Explains al-Majali's Cancellation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2204102394 Amman AKHIR KHABAR in Arabic 21-22 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2204102394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHIR KHABAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Nasir Qamash] </F>
  [Text] In a statement to AKHIR KHABAR, Information Minister 
Dr. Jawad al-'Anani has said several reasons led to Prime 
Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali's decision to cancel his 
visit to Bucharest, where he was due to participate in the Grans 
Montana Forum, in which politicians and businessmen from Europe 
and the Middle East take part. 
  He said the most prominent of these reasons is the 
inauguration of the extraordinary session of the House of 
Representatives, and the rumors that Prime Minister al-Majali 
would meet with Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres at the 
sidelines of the forum meetings. Al-'Anani said these reasons 
called for adopting the decision not to go. 
  Meanwhile, Dr. al-'Anani said Jordan was not officially 
informed of the schedule of U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher's tour in the region, and Jordan did not ask for 
this schedule. 
  Al-'Anani was answering a question on AFP report that 
Christopher will not stop in Amman and will meet with His 
Majesty King Husayn in London next Monday. 

</TEXT>

