<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crown Prince Receives Former Algerian President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crown Prince Receives Former Algerian President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2104190394 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1700 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2104190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Highness Crown Prince Hasan, the Regent, 
received former Algerian president Ahmed Ben Bella at the Royal 
Hashemite Court today. 
  During the meeting, the two sides discussed prospects of 
Arab 
cooperation and detente as well as efforts to clear the 
atmosphere and bolster inter-Arab relations. 
  President Ben Bella praised continued Jordanian efforts to 
protect the holy places in holy Jerusalem and to maintain the 
Arabism of Jerusalem against the Israeli siege imposed on it and 
Israel's continued efforts to Judaize it. 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified correspondent] Mr. 
President, could you give us an idea about your meeting with his 
highness the crown prince this morning? 
  [Ben Bella] I must say that I am not a visitor. I consider 
myself from this country. The crown prince is my brother. 
Frankly, it is a wedding day for me when I visit you. I came 
to take part in the celebrations of the third 
Hashemite-sponsored renovation of the al-Aqsa Mosque in 
Jerusalem. I came to see my brothers and ask about them. We 
are really proud of you all. 
  [Correspondent] Mr. President, how do you view talk in 
Algeria about prospects of dialogue between the Algerian 
Government and the Islamic Salvation Front? 
  [Ben Bella] It is a serious dialogue and I believe it will 
bear fruit soon, God willing. The situation in Algeria is 
difficult but not in the way it is being exaggerated outside. I 
mean the situation is not easy, but the process of reaching an 
agreement and achieving national reconciliation is going on. 
Many elements, including the new president, are seeking to 
achieve national reconciliation. 
  [Correspondent] The final question, Mr. President. 
Throughout your years of struggle, you always called for better 
inter-Arab relations for a better Arab future. How do you view 
inter-Arab relations now and efforts to clear the Arab 
atmosphere? 
  [Ben Bella] I am satisfied with this. The issue of unity is 
a given. We must unite. The world is uniting. Europe is 
uniting. America even united with Mexico. How can we not unite? 
We must unite. God willing, we will achieve unity even though 
this will take time and even though there are obstacles. 
However, we must unite. To be or not to be. We will unite, 
God willing. 
  [Correspondent] God willing, sir. 
  [Ben Bella] Our conscience is united. Regardless of what 
governments may think, our conscience is united. We must unite, 
God willing. 
  [Correspondent] God willing. Thank you Mr. President. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

