<H3> <TI>   Army Seizes FRC Camp, Detains Personnel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Seizes FRC Camp, Detains Personnel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2104122994 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1100 GMT 21 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2104122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We have just received the following report from the 
news desk: A Lebanese Army force of four troop carriers, four 
military vehicles, several Jeep-type vehicles, and about 75 
soldiers raided a camp belonging to the Fatah Revolutionary 
Council [FRC] located 1 km north of 'Ayta al-Fakhkhar, near 
Rashayya al-Wadi. 
  The Army confiscated the contents of the 20-room camp: four 
truckloads of cabinets, beds, military hardware, an automobile, 
and a water tanker. The Army took a number of FRC personnel 
into custody and closed down the camp. 

</TEXT>

