<H3> <TI>   Students Demonstrate Against UN `Silence' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Students Demonstrate Against UN `Silence' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104141794 Tehran IRNA in English 1151 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104141794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 21, IRNA -- Thousands of pupils and 
high school students staged demonstrations outside the U.N. 
office in Tehran Thursday, condemning the silence of the U.N., 
its Security Council and other international bodies on the 
massacre of Muslims in Gorazde. Carrying placards and banners 
in condemnation of the crimes of Serbs, the demonstrators 
chanted slogans such as "Serbs are committing crimes, Washington 
is supporting them" and "Death to the Serbs." They also called 
for resignation of the U.N. Secretary General Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali. 
  The students denounced the biased policies and shameful 
silence of western governments as well as the Security Council's 
negligence towards Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Similar demonstrations were held in front of the U.N. office 
by Iranian university students and in the holy city of Qom by 
ulama Wednesday in protest at the cold-blooded massacre of 
Muslims in Gorazde. 

</TEXT>

