<H3> <TI>   `Saboteurs' From Iran Blamed for 19 Apr Bombing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Saboteurs' From Iran Blamed for 19 Apr Bombing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104131894 Tehran IRNA in English 1229 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104131894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 21, IRNA -- Initial investigations 
into a bomb explosion in Tehran on Tuesday show that saboteurs 
infiltrating into Iran from Iraq were behind the blast, an 
informed source told IRNA Thursday. Members of Iraq-based 
terrorist Mujahideen Khalq Organization (MKO) have frequently 
used the bases and facilities put at their disposal by the Iraqi 
regime for carrying out terrorist acts inside Iran. 
  "Some clues have been obtained in connection with the bomb 
explosion at the corner of Sa'di and Enqelab streets (in central 
Tehran)," the source said. 
  Some 13 people were injured and five cars destroyed when a 
percussion bomb went off in rush hours Tuesday. A few hours 
after the bomb blast, the terrorist grouplet in a hasty reaction 
contacted the Italian news agency (ANSA), AFP and ASSOCIATED 
PRESS to deny its involvement in the terrorist act. 
  Over the past month, MKO in 23 radio contacts monitored by 
an 
IRNA office near Iran-Iraq border instructed its members to 
carry out sabotage and arson attacks on Iranian soil. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

