<H3> <TI>   President Receives Libyan Official, Message </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Receives Libyan Official, Message </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104114194 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Colonel Mustafa al-Karrubi, member of the Libyan 
leadership council, was received today by President 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani, to whom he presented a written message from 
the Libyan leader, Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi. 
  Conveying Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi's warm greetings to our 
country's president, Mr. Karrubi said the aim of his trip to 
Iran is to find ways of deepening fraternal relations between 
Iran and Libya and to activate the joint commission in order to 
increase the volume of economic and trade exchanges between the 
two countries. 
  He reported on the political and economic situation in Libya 
and said: The political and economic sanctions imposed on Libya 
by some Western countries are unjust and violate international 
law. 
  For his part, Hashemi-Rafsanjani expressed gratitude for the 
Libyan leader's friendly message. He said relations and 
cooperation between the two countries is at a good level and 
emphasized the need to expand them. 
  Referring to the political and economic pressure of world 
arrogance against independence-seeking countries, the president 
said the path of independence and refusal to surrender to the 
bullying which dominates the international order is filled with 
difficulties but leads to desirable results. 
  Hashemi-Rafsanjani also emphasized the need for a peaceful 
and just solution, through international organizations, to the 
existing differences between Libya and some Western countries. 

</TEXT>

