<H3> <TI>   Aid Convoy Leaves for Azerbaijani Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aid Convoy Leaves for Azerbaijani Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104201294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104201294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A convoy of relief aid for the Republic of 
Azerbaijan's Muslim refugees, comprising 36 trucks, today left 
the border post at Parsabad, in Moghan. This is the third 
convoy of aid sent by the Imam Khomeyni Relief Committee to the 
Republic of Azerbaijan. 
  According to an IRNA report the convoy is carrying 170 
tonnes 
of potatoes, 150 tonnes of flour, 1,000 blankets, 500 stoves and 
other facilities. The total value of the aid is 130 million 
rials. The relief aid dispatched to the Republic of Azerbaijan 
was collected by the imam relief committees in the provinces of 
Gilan, East Azarbaijan and Ardebil. 

