<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Australian Ambassador Comments on Trade Balance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Australian Ambassador Comments on Trade Balance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104163794 Tehran IRNA in English 1458 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tabriz, E. Azerbaijan, April 21, IRNA -- Volume of 
Trade exchanges between Iran and Australia reached dlrs. 
[dollars] 400 million last year, Australian Ambassador to Tehran 
Nicolas Warner told IRNA here Wednesday [20 April]. 
  Warner said during the period Iran's non-oil exports to 
Australia stood at dlrs. 25 million, up by 40 percent as 
compared with the amount of the preceding year. The exported 
commodities mainly included dried fruit and carpet, he added. 
  Australia has made some efforts to reduce the negative 
balance in the two countries' trade exchanges through organizing 
trade fairs and seminars for the Iranian exporters in several 
Australian cities. 
  Noting that Iran mainly imported wheat, meat and 
telecommunication equipment from Australia, Warner said his 
country had allocated dlrs. 750 million in credit for the 
Iranian importers in an effort to further consolidate mutual 
industrial and trade cooperation. 
  The ambassador visited this northwestern Iranian city to 
explore the grounds for the promotion of commercial cooperation 
between the provincial units and country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-13708 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes078_s_94016" </HT>


