<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dostum Militia General Killed by Hekmatyar Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dostum Militia General Killed by Hekmatyar Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104211794 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Dari 1600 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Dari </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] General Sakhi, known as Sakhi Broot, a militia 
general, was killed by Golboddin's militia in Dasht-e Saqawa 
south of Kabul in Logar Province. Security sources reported to 
BIA's correspondent that this professional criminal some days 
ago fought Golboddin's militia over looted goods; as a result of 
which he was killed along with his three bodyguards. The 
general's body still lies in Dasht-e Saqawa and is decomposing. 
No one has come to remove his body. Sakhi Broot some time ago 
stole the carpets of Sayed Abdolqader Jaylani mosque in Sayd Nur 
Mohammad Shah Mena, killed an innocent shepherd in the same 
area, and divided up his sheep among the militia. He was a 
notorious Dostum general and had a hand in many crimes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

