<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Rejects Opposition Charges on GATT </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Rejects Opposition Charges on GATT </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204031094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2204031094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The commerce minister has refuted the opposition's 
allegation that the government has compromised on the 
sovereignty of the nation by signing the GATT agreement at 
Marrakesh. 
  Giving clarifications on the statements regarding the 
Uruguay round of multilateral trade negotiations in Rajya Sabha 
today, Mr. Pranab Mukherjee asserted that the interest of the 
farmers and workers will not be affected by this treaty. Not 
satisfied with his clarification, almost the entire opposition 
staged a walkout, alleging that the government has bartered away 
the interests of the nation by signing the treaty. 
  Refuting the charges of the opposition that most of the 
foreign investment has come into the consumer sector, he said 90 
percent of the investment has been made into the core sector. 
Denying the charges that the center did not consult the chief 
ministers before signing the accord, he said he had talks with 
several chief ministers, including some of the non-Congress-I 
governments. 

</TEXT>

