<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Leaves for Medical Checkup in U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Leaves for Medical Checkup in U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204065894 Hong Kong AFP in English 0625 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2204065894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kathmandu, April 22 (AFP) -- Nepalese Prime Minister 
Girija Prasad Koirala left for Washington on Friday [22 April] 
to undergo a medical checkup, foreign ministry officials said 
here. 
  Koirala, who is is accompanied by sister-in-law Nona 
Koirala, 
his physician and others, will be examined at the Walter Reed 
Hospital near Washington. 
  The 72-year-old premier is scheduled to return within the 
next two weeks if there are no problems, officials said. 
  Koirala, who faces mounting pressure from within his party 
to 
quit, fainted twice times in public in the past six weeks. 
Doctors attributed the spells to low blood pressure and physical 
exhaustion. 

</TEXT>

