<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Regiment From Punjab Reportedly Sent to Kashmir </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Regiment From Punjab Reportedly Sent to Kashmir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204025594 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2204025594 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A full regiment, the Rashtriya Rifles, of the Indian 
Armed Forces, which was previously deployed in the Indian 
Punjab, has now been moved to Srinagar so that it can 
participate in crushing the freedom struggle in occupied Kashmir. 
  Meanwhile, nine more people, including four freedom 
fighters, 
one civilian and two Indian soldiers, have been killed in fresh 
clashes at Baramula and other places. Two persons were killed 
while under police custody in Gandarbal. Many people have been 
injured as a result of indiscriminate firing by the Indian 
forces at Batapura in Badgam. The freedom fighters attacked the 
Army patrols in Kundi, Karibamalu, and the Kariba Zohra area of 
Shupiyan, injuring several soldiers. 

</TEXT>

