<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supreme Court Orders Restoration of NWFP Assembly </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Supreme Court Orders Restoration of NWFP Assembly </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204020994 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2204020994 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Supreme Court of Pakistan has by a majority vote 
held that on the revival of the Provincial Assembly of the NWFP 
[North-West Frontier Province] on the lapse of the proclamation 
issued by the president, the chief minister and his cabinet will 
stand revived. 
  The court clarified that it would be open to the governor to 
refix the date and time in accordance with Article 130 (5) of 
the Constitution, requiring the chief minister to obtain a vote 
of confidence from the assembly. 
  The two dissenting judges were of the view that the petition 
[by the former chief minister] was not maintainable and would 
therefore stand dismissed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

