<H3> <TI>   Commander Says Implementing Accord Could End Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commander Says Implementing Accord Could End Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2104123094 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0924 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2104123094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 21 Apr (INA) -- A prominent Yemeni commander 
has said that implementing the Yemeni document of pledge and 
accord and withdrawing the military units from the previous 
areas of partition is the way to end the current Yemeni crisis. 
  In statements published by the newspaper 26 SEPTEMBER, 
mouthpiece of the Yemeni Armed Forces, today, Brigadier General 
'Abd-al-Malik (al-Sabati), Yemeni chief of staff, revealed that 
a military plan is being prepared which contains numerous 
measures to withdraw the military forces to new strategic areas 
in six Yemeni governorates. He added that this plan aims to 
remove military tension and keep the military units away from 
the previous areas of partition. 

</TEXT>

