<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnian Envoy Says Gorazde Fall `Western Plot' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bosnian Envoy Says Gorazde Fall `Western Plot' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104114394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Bosnian ambassador to Tehran has termed the fall 
of Gorazde a pre-planned Western plot. In an interview with our 
reporter, Mr. Omar Bahman emphasized that the UN and Security 
Council member countries, including Britain, France, and Russia 
were directly responsible for the massacre of Gorazde Muslims. 
  In reference to activities of the UN secretary general, he 
said: Butrus-Ghali and other UN officials are receiving huge 
salaries from the international budget to guard the interests of 
powerful countries. 
  The Bosnian ambassador also called on Islamic countries to 
show greater movement toward solving the Bosnian crisis. Mr. 
Omar Bahman said: Islamic Conference Organization resolutions, 
much like UN resolutions, have remained as paper documents. He 
said that a number of Islamic countries, in particular Arab 
governments, which are similar to Western countries and act to 
deceive public opinion, support Bosnia only in words. 
  Thanking Tehran for its stance, the Bosnian ambassador said: 
The practical support provided by the people and government of 
Iran for the Bosnian nation was an appreciated reality. 

</TEXT>

