<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranian, Indian Ministers Discuss GATT, Employment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iranian, Indian Ministers Discuss GATT, Employment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204041494 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network in English 
1630 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2204041494 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi Doordarshan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iran says it fully supports India's stand that 
social issues like labor should not be used to dilute the 
multilateral GATT treaty. The Iranian labor minister, Mr. 
Hoseyn Kamali, conveyed this to the labor minister, Mr. P.A. 
Sangma, during their meeting in New Delhi. They also discussed 
the forthcoming labor ministers conference of nonaligned 
countries where this issue will be taken up for discussion. The 
two sides reviewed issues connected with the employment of 
workers in each other's countries. 

</TEXT>

