<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   Musa Cited on Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa Cited on Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2404105294 Abu Dhabi United Arab Emirates Radio Network in 
Arabic 0930 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2404105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Abu Dhabi United Arab Emirates Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] A session of talks was held at al-Mushrif Palace 
this morning between His Highness Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan Al 
Nuhayyan, President of the United Arab Emirates, and his brother 
His Excellency President Muhmmad Husni Mubarak of sisterly 
Egypt. [passage omitted] 
  After the expanded meeting, a meeting confined to the two 
leaders was held. 
  Egyptian Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has stated that today's 
main session of talks between the two leaders dealt with the 
developments in the Gulf region and Arab developments in 
general, the Middle East peace process, the results of the two 
leaders' mediation to preserve Yemeni unity, the situation in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, and bilateral ties in the economic and 
technical fields. 
  In a statement to the EMIRATES NEWS AGENCY, Musa said that 
the two leaders noted their eagerness and efforts to preserve 
Yemeni Unity and implement the Yemeni Pledge and Accord 
Document. He noted that Badr Hammam, the assistant Egyptian 
foreign minister, is now in Sanaa to pursue contacts between 
Yemeni leaders in Sanaa and Aden. 
  Answering a question on whether the talks dealt with 
arrangements to hold a quadrilateral Arab summit in Cairo to 
deal with the Yemeni situation, Musa said that preparations have 
not been made to hold this summit but the idea is still there. 
This summit would require good planning to ensure its success. 
  Musa said that the two leaders expressed great interest in 
developments in Bosnia-Hrezegovina and stressed the need for the 
international community to end the Serb attack against the 
people of Gorazde. Musa praised the NATO ultimatum to attack 
Serb forces unless they withdrew from Gorazde and said that he 
considered this a good move in the right direction if it 
realizes the aim of stopping Serb attacks and establishing peace 
in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

