<F P=102>   JN2304173394 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1600 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2304173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Colonel Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi this afternoon 
received Hamid Yusuf Hammadi, President Saddam Husayn's envoy 
and minister of culture and information. The leader president's 
envoy conveyed a message from his excellency on Iraq's view of 
the situation at the UN Security Council, relations with the UN 
Social Commission, which is headed by Rolf Ekeus, and Iraq's 
implementation of the provisions of Part C of UN Security 
Council Resolution No. 687. The message stresses the importance 
of coordination among sisterly and friendly states to work to 
lift the unjust blockade imposed on Iraq. 
  Colonel al-Qadhdhafi expressed Libya's solidarity with Iraq 
and his support for the recent Iraqi move. 
  The meeting was attended by Jum'ah al-Fazzani, secretary of 
the General People's Committee for Unity, and the Iraqi 
ambassador in Libya. 

