<H3> <TI>   Harakat-e Eslami Statement Denounces Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Harakat-e Eslami Statement Denounces Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304201194 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304201194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In issuing a statement, the Harakat-e Eslami-ye 
Afghanistan [Islamic Movement of Afghanistan] has said: This 
party will not remain indifferent and will take necessary action 
via-a-vis those individuals who for their self-interest intend 
to disrupt peace and security in the west of Kabul and attempt 
to stir up the fighting once again. Highlighting the tragic and 
painful events of the past two years in the west of Kabul, 
resulting in insecurity, destruction, and fratricide, and 
bringing various calamities to the people, the statement 
denounces every terrorist and adventurist action. 
  The statement adds: The Harakat-e Eslami emphasizes its 
peace-seeking policy and supports the atmosphere of peace and 
understanding, and regards talks and understanding as the only 
way to a solution of the existing issues in the country. 
  This statement has been issued after sporadic clashes 
started 
two days ago in Kabul city by irresponsible individuals. The 
responsible officials of the belligerent sides also denounced 
these clashes and have managed to stop this fire. 

</TEXT>

