1400 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2204145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In occupied Kashmir, 12 Indian troops were killed 
when mojahedin launched a retaliatory attack on military camp 
near (Dandalgam). Several soldiers were also injured in the 
attack. 
  Meanwhile, Indian troops martyred another six persons during 
siege and search operations at various places in the valley. 
Two persons were killed in an indiscriminate firing by the 
troops in Sopor District, while two mojahedin fell in a clash at 
(Gulzar Tangmarg). A brutal crackdown was carried out in the 
suburban areas of Srinagar. People were forced to come out of 
their houses for searches and were made to stand in the open for 
hours. Over 50 people, mostly youths, were rounded up during 
the operation. Three people were seriously injured when a bomb 
exploded in Jammu region. 

