GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2504064494 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali has said 
Pakistan is pursuing a foreign policy based on national 
interests, which has the definite direction and the thrust to 
achieve major objectives. In an interview in Islamabad, he said 
the Kashmir issue has been internationalized in a successful 
manner and that initiatives have been taken for peace in 
Afghanistan and Tajikistan. Such initiatives have also been 
taken regarding Somalia and Bosnia. 
  The foreign minister said Pakistan has been successful in 
securing U.S. agreement not to press for a rollback of its 
nuclear program. Reviewing the achievements of the present 
government in the foreign affairs, Asif Ali expressed the 
confidence that Pakistan will be able to acquire the F-16 
aircraft without compromising its fundamental stand on nuclear 
nonproliferation. He said Pakistan has refused to accept any 
unilateral and discriminatory conditions on the nuclear issue. 

</TEXT>

