<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iraqi Speaker, Parliamentary Delegation Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraqi Speaker, Parliamentary Delegation Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2404145794 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2404145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A four-member Iraqi parliamentary delegation led by 
the speaker of National Assembly, Sa'di Mahdi Salih, arrived in 
Islamabad today on a four-day official visit. Talking to 
newsmen at the airport, the leader of the delegation said human 
rights of the Kashmiri people must be respected and the Kashmir 
issue should be resolved peacefully. He said the purpose of his 
visit is to bring the people of the two countries closer to each 
other so that they could have better understanding. 
  Later, the speaker of National Assembly of Iraq called on 
his 
Pakistani counterpart in Islamabad. During the meeting, the two 
leaders agreed that closer cooperation among Muslim countries is 
required to face the challenges posed by the current world 
situation. They also discussed matters relating to 
establishment of IPU [Inter-Parliamentary Union] of Muslim 
countries, holding of a women parliamentarian conference, and 
establishment of friendship groups in their respective 
parliaments. Syed Yusuf Raza Gilani said the government and 
people of Pakistan were really distressed by the magnitude of 
suffering of the Iraqi people. He said there should be no 
restrictions on the supply of food and medicines to Iraqi 
people. The speaker of National Assembly of Iraq, Mr. Sa'di 
Mahdi Salih, warmly reciprocated the views and feelings of Syed 
Yusuf Raza Gilani. He appreciated the geopolitical importance 
of Pakistan and the role played by it in regional and world 
affairs. 

</TEXT>

