<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rabat, 23 Apr (INA) -- Barzan al-Tikriti, personal 
envoy of leader President Saddam Husayn, has relayed a message 
from his excellency the president to his brother King Hassan II 
of Morocco on the fraternal bilateral ties between Iraq and 
Morocco and the relationship between Iraq and the UN Security 
Council after Iraq honored its commitments to the relevant UN 
Security Council resolutions. The message underscores that this 
requires the UN Security Council to fulfill its commitments by 
lifting the embargo clamped on Iraq. 
  The president's message was communicated to the Moroccan 
monarch during a meeting he held with the Iraqi envoy yesterday. 
During the meeting, King Hassan II expressed his thanks to His 
Excellency President Saddam Husayn for keeping him informed of 
the Iraqi position, and also of the recent developments in the 
relationship with the UN Security Council. He reiterated 
Morocco's support for the Iraqi Government and people. 
  The Moroccan monarch asserted that Iraq has done all it is 
required to do on both the Arab and international scenes, and 
that there is no longer any justification for maintaining the 
current state of affairs. 
  King Hassan II of Morocco asked Barzan al-Tikriti to relay 
his greetings to His Excellency President Saddam Husayn. 
  The meeting was attended by Abdellatif Filali, Moroccan 
minister of state for foreign affairs and cooperation; Abdelhadi 
Boutaleb [name as received], adviser to King Hassan II; and the 
Iraqi ambassador in Rabat. 

</TEXT>

