<F P=102>   EA2204190394 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 0430 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2204190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lieutenant General 'Umar Hasan Ahmad al-Bashir, the 
president of the Republic, has again denied the U.S. allegations 
about Sudan's violation of human rights and support for 
terrorism. The president made this denial yesterday in an 
interview with Russian television, in his office at the general 
command of the people's armed forces. During the interview Lt. 
Gen. al-Bashir also talked about political, economic and social 
developments in Sudan, as well as Russian-Sudanese relations. 
  Russian television also conducted an interview with the 
minister of state at the Foreign Ministry, Archbishop Gabriel 
Rodge, during which he explained that his participation in 
government is for the sake of the country's unity and 
advancement. He said that there is no religious problem in 
Sudan as portrayed by the Western mass media. He explained that 
the Government of Sudan is serious in its efforts to solve the 
southern problem. He said that Sudan enjoys a normal life in 
which peaceful coexistence prevails. Regarding conditions in 
the south of the country, the minister of state at the Foreign 
Ministry noted that the situation is very stable, which suggests 
that the achievement of a comprehensive peace in a unified Sudan 
is getting closer. 

</TEXT>

