  [Excerpt] The provincial federation of the General Union of 
Algerian Workers [UGTA] in Biskra held its fifth congress at the 
university center at the end of this week with the attendance of 
the UGTA secretary general Abdelhak Benhamouda and members of 
the national secretariat. The congress is being held with a 
view to appointing the provincial executive committee and the 
secretariat of the federation. Abdelkarim Benmoufaq reports: 
  [Benmoufaq] The congress was opened by UGTA secretary 
general 
Abdelhak Benhamouda. He delivered a lengthy speech on the 
occasion, in which he dealt with workers' difficulties in light 
of the fall in purchasing power. Soaring prices and a 
deterioration in the country's general situation, he said, has 
negatively effected workers and is a threat to their future. 
  In another development, he pointed out the plots hatched to 
harm the UGTA because it had worried many people because UGTA 
had been able to absorb and bring together workers and bring 
about a qualitative development on many issues that concerned 
the workers' stratum. He also stressed UGTA's determination to 
continue a real and effective trade union struggle now to try to 
protect workers' interests and defend their rights. [passage 
omitted] 

