<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Complains About Israeli `Terrorist Methods' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Complains About Israeli `Terrorist Methods' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2404102794 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0940 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2404102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 24 Apr (INA)--Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat has sent messages to the heads of the Security Council 
permanent member states, the chairman of the Nonaligned 
Movement, and the secretary general of the Arab League in which 
he complained about the Zionist entity and the terrorist methods 
it employs against the Palestinian people and the PLO. 
  A Palestinian official told an INA correspondent in Cairo 
that in his written message, 'Arafat said the Zionist entity 
maneuvers to swallow the Palestinians and to politically 
liquidate them, and that the PLO has offered the Zionist entity 
all it asked for. 

</TEXT>

