<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Asks Fatah To Collect, Store Away Weapons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO Asks Fatah To Collect, Store Away Weapons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2304080294 Beirut AL-DIYAR in Arabic 13 Apr 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> NC2304080294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut AL-DIYAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mahmud Zayyat] </F>
  [Excerpt] The PLO leadership has asked Fatah leaders in 
Lebanon to collect and store weapons in the camps of the south 
in preparation for their transfer to Gaza and Jericho under 
Egyptian supervision, an informed Palestinian source disclosed. 
The source noted that prices of weapons on the world market 
have gone up. 
  The source said that Fatah official in Tyre Sultan 
Abu-al-'Aynayn, a supporter of Yasir 'Arafat, began collecting 
weapons in the camps of the region under his supervision. 
  The source said the move is part of an effort to remove 
weapons from the camps to influence the Palestinian forces that 
oppose Gaza-Jericho agreement and paralyze their activity in 
resisting the Israeli occupation of the south. The source noted 
that representatives of factions opposing the PLO policy and 
opposition Fatah leaders led by Colonel Munir al-Maqdah have 
recently held a series of meetings to escalate military action 
against the Israeli occupation forces in the south, and even in 
northern Palestine (Upper Galilee). This was evident in the 
operation carried out jointly by the George Habash-led Popular 
Front for the Liberation of Palestine and al-Maqdah group in 
al-Khardali. Three fighters were killed in the operation. 
  The source described the collection of weapons and their 
transfer to Gaza and Jericho as a new card that will be conceded 
in favor of 'Arafat's capitulatory policy. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

