<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qaddumi, World Bank Delegation Sign Agreements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qaddumi, World Bank Delegation Sign Agreements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204182894 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2204182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Abu-Lutf [Faruq Qaddumi], head of the PLO's 
Political Department and acting chairman of the governors 
committee, has met with a delegation of the World Bank, led by 
Ram Shabra. 
  Brother Abu-Lutf said that the atmosphere at the meeting was 
positive and that it focused on core issues between the World 
Bank, as the secretariat of the donor countries [as heard], and 
the PLO. A number of agreements were signed. They will be 
submitted to the PLO's Executive Committee. These agreements 
concern the financing of the temporary working budget of the 
Palestinian Economic Council of Development and Construction to 
enable it to continue its work and to implement the plans that 
have been approved by the Palestinian national authority, the 
donor countries and the World Bank, as assigned by the PLO. 
  Brother Abu-Lutf said that a series of coordination meetings 
between the presidency of the World Bank would take place within 
the next few days with a view to expediting the execution of the 
plans agreed on between by the Palestinian national authority, 
donor countries and the World Bank, and which concern the 
reconstruction of the Palestinian national economy. 

</TEXT>

