<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Puts `Freeze' on Timetable for PLO Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin Puts `Freeze' on Timetable for PLO Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2504075894 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 25 Apr 94 pp A1, A10 </F>
<F P=103> TA2504075894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Yerah Tal, Aluf Ben, Gay Bekhor, and news </F>
agencies] 
  [Excerpt] Yesterday Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin put a 
freeze on the accelerated timetable for the completion of the 
talks with the PLO which Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres and PLO 
Chairman Yasir 'Arafat agreed on during their meetings in 
Bucharest last week. In view of the prime minister's 
reservations, there is doubt that the Peres-'Arafat meeting, 
scheduled for 28 April in Cairo, will indeed take place as 
planned. The final decision regarding the date of that meeting 
has been put off until after Rabin returns from Russia on 28 
April. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

