<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres' Bureau Denies Differences With Rabin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres' Bureau Denies Differences With Rabin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2404132194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 24 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2404132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres' bureau announced 
that there is total agreement between Mr. Peres and Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin on the tactics and path to be taken in 
the negotiations with the PLO. Our correspondent Hayim Hecht 
reports that this was said in response to the report that there 
are differences of opinion between the two on the negotiations 
with the Palestinians, which are focused on the issue of whether 
Israel must sign an agreement within two weeks. 

</TEXT>

