<H3> <TI>   Peres: Rabin Remarks Call For Signal From Syria </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres: Rabin Remarks Call For Signal From Syria </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2404100194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 24 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2404100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres said that now, 
following Prime Minister Rabin's statements on the readiness to 
evacuate settlements on the Golan Heights in exchange for peace, 
Syrian President al-Asad had good reason to emit positive 
signals toward Israel. The foreign minister told our 
correspondent Hayim Hecht that the change indicated by Rabin's 
remarks lay in the statement itself and not in its content. The 
foreign minister added that the government realized that Syria 
was always slow to react. 

</TEXT>

