<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Off to Moscow; Peres Expects Intense PLO Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin Off to Moscow; Peres Expects Intense PLO Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2404064194 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0630 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2404064194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin left for an official 
four-day visit to Moscow several minutes ago. Foreign Minister 
Shim'on Peres, who together with the rest of the cabinet 
ministers accompanied Rabin to his flight, said that very 
intensive negotiations with the Palestinians were expected this 
week. If everything went well, Peres said, the negotiations may 
be concluded this week. If this does not turn out to be the 
case, the foreign minister added, we will have to find ways to 
accelerate the talks. This was reported by our correspondent 
Yariv Ben-Yehuda from Ben-Gurion airport. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

