<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Employment of 4,000 Palestinians Authorized </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Employment of 4,000 Palestinians Authorized </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2404063194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0600 GMT 24 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2404063194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin has authorized the 
entry of another 4,000 Palestinian laborers from the territories 
to work in Israel. Approximately half of them will be employed 
in industry while the other half will work in agriculture. This 
authorization applies to married Palestinians over the age of 27 
who have worked in Israel for over five years. 
  Our correspondent 'Ofra Nehman notes that with the addition 
of these workers, the number of laborers from the territories 
working in Israel is now equal to the number of those employed 
prior to the decision to impose a full closure. 

</TEXT>

