<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Labor Party Expels Ramon, 2 Other MK's </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2104170294 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1400 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2104170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by party affairs correspondent Sefi Handler] </F>
  [Excerpt] With about a 24-hour delay, Knesset Members 
[MK's] Hayim Ramon, 'Amir Peretz, and Shmu'el Avital today 
received letters expelling them from the Labor party. The 
letters, sent by the Labor headquarters, advised them that under 
the party constitution, they are no longer Labor members. The 
other Labor members included in Ramon's Histadrut elections list 
will receive similar letters after the headquarters check the 
matter with each of them. [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 
1600 GMT on 21 April cites the Labor spokesman as saying that 
"the Ramon list includes 25 Labor members, and they will receive 
expulsion letters tonight and tomorrow. MK Ramon has said that 
the list he had submitted to the election committee includes 300 
to 400 Labor members."] 
  Meanwhile, Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin again attacked the 
Ramon list which, he said, is liable to harm the peace process. 
Addressing the United Kibbutzim Movement convention in Ramat 
Ef'al today, the prime minister again warned: Ramon and his 
list will harm the government operation. [passage omitted] 

