<H3> <TI>   Officials Comment on Bosnia, Assistance for Muslims </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials Comment on Bosnia, Assistance for Muslims </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Minister on Military Assistance </H4>

<F P=102> LD2204151494 Tehran IRNA in English 1426 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Semnan, April 22, IRNA -- Defence Minister Mohammad 
Foruzandeh said here last night that the Armed Forces of Iran 
are ready to offer support for the Muslim Bosnians. 
  He referred to the recent speech of the commander in chief 
of 
the Armed Forces of the Islamic Repubic of Iran and said the 
Armed Forces are ready to offer every type of assistance to 
Bosnian Muslims and defend them against the Serbs. 
  He said the Islamic Republic now has a grave responsibility 
for building a new civilization which needs sacrifice and 
material resources, human resources, and thought. 
  The meeting was attended by commanders of the armed forces 
in 
Semnan (300 kms east of Tehran). 

</TEXT>

