<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Comment on Bosnia, Assistance for Muslims </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials Comment on Bosnia, Assistance for Muslims </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Security Council Discusses Bosnia </H4>

<F P=102> LD2304200494 Tehran IRIB Television Second Program Network 
in Persian 1800 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television Second Program Network 
in Persian 1800 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In today's meeting of the Supreme National Security 
Council, which was chaired by President Hashemi-Rafsanjani and 
was attended by all members and high ranking military 
commanders, the latest developments relating to 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and the tragedy of Gorazde were discussed. 
  The attacks and crimes of the Serbian forces were condemned 
and it was announced that the UN Security Council and countries 
that had given the aggressors a free hand by their indifference 
shared the blame for this immense human tragedy. 
  It was stressed in the meeting that, in view of the lack of 
seriousness shown by the United Nations and NATO regarding the 
defense of regions which had been declared as safe havens in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, our country's Foreign Ministry should act 
with even greater resolve towards strengthening the effective 
cooperation between Islamic countries with a view to lifting the 
arms embargo on Bosnia. 
  It was also decided that the government would set about 
gathering extensive relief aid to help the defenseless people of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  In view of the guidance issued by the eminent leader 
[Khamene'i], the constructive role that could be played by 
peacekeeping forces from Islamic countries in Bosnia-Herzegovina 
was also underlined. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

