<H3> <TI>   Officials Comment on Bosnia, Assistance for Muslims </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials Comment on Bosnia, Assistance for Muslims </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Speaker Urges Lifting of Arms Embargo </H4>

<F P=102> LD2404090494 Tehran IRNA in English 0838 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 24, IRNA -- Majles Speaker Hojjat 
ol-Eslam 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri here Sunday [24 April] called on 
Islamic countries to lift arms embargo against Muslims in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Speaking at today's Majles open session, the speaker 
referred 
to the support of the international bodies, including the U.N. 
and hegemonist powers, for the Serbian crimes and said, "Islamic 
countries, given the unreliability of U.N. Security Council 
resolutions, should lift the arms embargo against Bosnia to 
enable the Muslims in that country to defend themselves." 
  He expressed hope that Islamic countries would not limit 
themselves to uttering words but would also enter the scene of 
action. 
  The speaker referred to his recent talks with Malaysian and 
Pakistani officials and said authorities in the two countries 
held identical views in connection with the double standard of 
the internatiional community on Bosnia and its inaction in 
standing against the Serbs aggressions. 
  He also condemned the failed attempt against the life of 
Hojjat ol-Eslam Abaie, susbstitute Friday prayer leader of 
Mashhad, by terrorist groups and called on the Information 
Ministry to take a serious stance towards the issue. 
  "Those lackey munafiq (hypocrite) elements should know that 
by resorting to such assassination attempts and explosions they 
could not disappoint the ulema and the people to abandon their 
struggle and could not create a state of terror in the society," 
remarked the speaker. 

</TEXT>

