<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mr. 'Ali Akbar Velayati, our country's foreign 
minister, who has gone to Romania in order to attend the general 
session of the World Forum Foundation, has met that country's 
president and, as well as conveying the warm greetings of 
President Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani, has expressed the anxiety 
felt by Islamic countries about the situation of Bosnian Muslims. 
  In the meeting, Romanian President Ion Iliescu spoke of the 
bilateral relations between Iran and Romania and called for the 
expansion of political and economic ties between the two 
countries. 
  Also today, on the third day of the current session of the 
World Forum Foundation, Mr. Velayati, who was in the chair, 
spoke about our country's economic capabilities and about those 
of Central Asian countries. In the meeting, which was attended 
by the representatives of most countries, discussions were held 
about the pipeline for the transfer of gas and oil from 
Turkmenistan and Kazakhstan to Europe via Iran. 

