<H3> <TI>   Returns, Comments on Forum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Returns, Comments on Forum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2404074394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0330 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2404074394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Velayati, our foreign minister, who went to 
Romania to participate in the World Forum Foundation, returned 
to Tehran at midnight. He said that Bosnia-Herzegovina and the 
Serbs' atrocities against the Muslims of that country, 
especially in Gorazde, were the main topics of his discussions 
with the Croatian parliamentary speaker and the foreign 
ministers of Albania, Romania, and Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  In an exclusive interview with our correspondent on the 
World 
Forum Foundation, Dr. Velayati said: 
  [Begin Velayati recording] The forum, which was established 
five years ago, is a nongovernmental international center that 
usually meets once a year in the month of Tir [22 June-22 July] 
at Crans-Montana in Switzerland. In some countries, an 
emergency session is held on request to discuss specific issues 
between the annual sessions. Therefore, this is a new form of 
international gathering that is, as I mentioned, a 
nongovernmental one and is progressing alongside the United 
Nations and other affiliated organizations. 
  The first session of this kind was held in Davos, 
Switzerland 
and the second one was convened in Crans-Montana [as heard]. In 
other parts of the world, similar organizations are being 
established. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

