<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Debt Payments to Denmark Rescheduled </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Debt Payments to Denmark Rescheduled </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504082694 Tehran IRNA in English 0755 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2504082694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 25, IRNA -- The governor of the 
Central Bank of Iran Mohammad Hoseyn 'Adeli Sunday announced 
that Iran and Denmark have reached an agreement for rescheduling 
the payment of Iran's delayed debts. 
  'Adeli, who is currently in Washington D.C. to attend the 
joint session of the World Bank and International Monetary Fund, 
told IRNA Sunday that Denmark has agreed to grant a credit of 
dlrs. 210 million to Iran for the payment of its debts including 
those scheduled for 1994-5. 
  Therefore, he added, the total debts of Iran to Denmark are 
rescheduled to be paid off within a period of six years, he said. 
  He also added that some of the German corporations have also 
agreed to reschedule the payment of German marks 520 million of 
Iran's debts. 

</TEXT>

