<F P=103> NC2404132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 24 Apr (MENA)--Egypt, the current OAU 
chairman, has urged the nationalist forces in South Africa to 
end all acts of violence and prepare for free and honest 
elections that will establish a democratic system in which all 
sides can participate. This was stated by a responsible source 
at the Foreign Ministry on the occasion of the first non-racial 
elections to be held in South Africa on Tuesday. 
  The Egyptian source said that the current stage in which 
democratic changes are taking place in South Africa demands 
extreme vigilance because it is difficult to eliminate the 
legacy of racism and tribalism in a very short time. 
  He added that the elections require the support of all 
local, 
regional, and international political forces to thwart the plans 
of the enemies of democracy. 
  The source affirmed that the democratic changes in South 
Africa are consistent with the views and will of the 
international community. He added that attempts to frustrate 
these changes will fail because they are not in the interest of 
the South African people. 

</TEXT>

