<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper Praises Lebanon's Severing Ties With Iraq </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2404071194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0605 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2404071194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 24 Apr (MENA)--AL-AKHBAR praises the Lebanese 
Government's stance on the recent assassination of the Iraqi 
opposition figure in Beirut, describing it as courageous and 
decisive. 
  The paper says in its editorial today that the Lebanese 
Government first asked the Baghdad Government to lift the 
diplomatic immunity of the perpetrators of the crime so they 
could be brought to trial. When the Iraqi Foreign Ministry 
refused, Lebanon immediately announced the severance of 
diplomatic ties with Iraq. 
  AL-AKHBAR adds that this incident reaffirms the Iraqi 
regime's continued involvement in terrorist acts and President 
Saddam Husayn's insistence on continuing to liquidate his 
opponents abroad. The incident also reaffirms that any attempt 
to improve ties with the Iraqi regime or to have confidence in 
it is useless. 
  In conclusion, the paper says it is regrettable that the 
assassination of the Iraqi opposition figure in Beirut came at a 
time when some have been calling for Arab unity and Arab 
solidarity. 

</TEXT>

