<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Asyut, Egypt, April 24 (AFP)--Egyptian authorities 
seized a quantity of explosives here Saturday that Islamic 
fundamentalists planned to use in attacks, a source close to the 
security forces said. 
  The haul followed information given by three "dangerous" 
fundamentalists arrested at Tahta in Suhaj Province south of 
Asyut, the source said. 
  Comprising 16 detonators and 10 kilos (22 pounds) of TNT, it 
was found in a cemetery at al-Badari, 410 kilometres (250 miles) 
south of Cairo. 

