<H3> <TI>   Head of UN Special Commission Arrives, Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Head of UN Special Commission Arrives, Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2404130094 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1210 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2404130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 24 Apr (INA) -- Rolf Ekeus, head of the UN 
Security Council's Special Commission, arrived in Baghdad at 
noon today at the head of a delegation on a two-day visit to 
Iraq. 
  In a statement to the IRAQI NEWS AGENCY, Rolf Ekeus said 
that 
he would resume the talks he began with Iraqi officials in New 
York and Baghdad in July, 1993, which resulted in tangible 
progress. 
  Asked whether the visit was part of the dialogue between 
Iraq 
and the Special Commission, Ekeus said that the UN Security 
Council welcomed the visit, endorsed it, and asked for an early 
report on the results of these talks, and that the Special 
Commission promised to present the report to the Security 
Council next week. 
  Ekeus also clarified that talks with the Iraqi side will 
deal 
with political and technical aspects. 
  The Special Commission consists of Maurizio Zifferero, 
deputy 
chairman of the International Atomic Energy Agency; Tim Trigan 
[name as transliterated], spokesman for the UN Special 
Commission; and a number of technicians. 
  The IRAQI NEWS AGENCY has learned that the talks between 
Iraq 
and the Special Commission will begin at the Foreign Ministry 
tomorrow evening. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

