<H3> <TI>   Saddam Receives Libyan Leader's Envoy, Letter </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Receives Libyan Leader's Envoy, Letter </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2404141294 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1318 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2404141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 24 Apr (INA) -- President Saddam Husayn has 
received Mustafa al-Kharrubi, personal envoy to his excellency 
from his brother Libyan President Colonel Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi. 
  Col. Mustafa al-Kharrubi conveyed to his excellency the 
president a letter from his brother Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi 
dealing with relations between the two brotherly countries, as 
well as issues of common interest. 
  President Saddam Husayn asserted to the Libyan envoy Iraq's 
firm support for fraternal Libya against hostile plans targeting 
it. 
  Col. Mustafa al-Kharrubi expressed to his excellency the 
support of the Libyan Government and people for fraternal Iraq 
in its just and legitimate struggle to confront the unjust 
blockade with all means. He also praised the steadfastness and 
firmness of our Iraqi mujahid people. 
  Col. Mustafa al-Kharrubi was accompanied by Ahmad 
'Abd-al-Salam Bin-Khayyal, under secretary at the Secretariat of 
the General People's Congress for Foreign Affairs. 
  The meeting was attended by Tariq 'Aziz, member of the 
Revolution Command Council and deputy prime minister, and 
'Abd-al-Jabbar 'Umar, Foreign Ministry under secretary. 

</TEXT>

