<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 23 Apr (INA)--Vice President Taha Yasin 
Ramadan met this evening with Colonel Mustafa al-Kharrubi, 
personal envoy of Libyan President Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi to his 
brother President Saddam Husayn, at his residence. The two 
officials reviewed forms of U.S.-Zionist plots concocted against 
Iraq and Libya. They also discussed ways of cooperation and 
coordination between the two sides to confront the challenges 
imposed on the two countries, particularly the continuation of 
the unjust blockade on the two fraternal people. 
  Col. Mustafa al-Kharrubi arrived in Baghdad today on a visit 
of several days. He is accompanied by Ahmad 'Abd-al-Salam 
Bin-Khayyal, official at the General People's Committee for 
External Liaison, and Husayn Salih, director of the Arab League 
Affairs at the General People's Committee for Unity. 
  INA learned that Col. Mustafa al-Kharrubi is bringing a 
personal message to President Saddam Husayn from his brother 
Libyan President Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi. 

