<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Aziz Meets Jordanian Islamic Action Front Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Aziz Meets Jordanian Islamic Action Front Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2304134594 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1143 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2304134594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 23 Apr (INA) -- Tariq 'Aziz, official in 
charge of the Foreign Relations Bureau of the Arab Socialist 
Ba'th Party, today received here a Jordanian Islamic Action 
Front delegation. The delegation, which is currently visiting 
the country, is led by 'Abdallah al-'Akayilah. 
  Tariq 'Aziz stressed that thanks to the wisdom of President 
Saddam Husayn and the resolve of the Iraqi people, Iraq has 
managed to rebuild what the evil and arrogant forces have 
destroyed, despite the continuation of the unjust blockade 
against it. He said that when people have sincere and faithful 
leaders with clear objectives, they manage to hold fast and 
attain their objectives. Such is the case in Iraq, he noted. 
He added: Despite all difficulties, we in Iraq are optimistic 
about the future. 
  Al-'Akayilah praised the Iraqi people's steadfastness and 
courage in confronting the aggressors and the iniquitous 
blockade. He said that Iraq has initiated the phenomenon of 
defying the world's arrogant powers, and that Iraq represents 
the Arab nation's ammunition for confronting the serious plot 
targeting Arabism and Islam. 
  The two sides stressed the importance of cooperation and 
coordination between pan-Arabist and Islamic forces and 
movements in the joint struggle against the imperialist and 
Zionist plots and threats. 

</TEXT>

