<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sources on `Expected' Tripartite Meeting 28 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sources on `Expected' Tripartite Meeting 28 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2304124194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1200 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2304124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cairo, 23 Apr (MENA) -- Informed Palestinian 
sources in Cairo expect a tripartite meeting to be held in Cairo 
on 28 April with Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat, Israeli 
Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres, and U.S. Secretary of State 
Warren Christopher to agree on a date to implement the 
Gaza-Jericho agreement and eliminate the obstacles hindering 
Palestinian-Israeli talks. 
  The sources told MENA that if the remaining points of 
difference are resolved during the coming round of talks that 
will begin in Cairo tomorrow, Wednesday [as received], a summit 
meeting is expected to be held between 'Arafat and Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin in Cairo on 2 May. That summit will 
discuss an agreement on the area of Jericho, which was left to 
the two leaders, and the issuance of passports for Palestinians 
in Gaza and Jericho. 
  According to the same sources, the final signing of the 
agreement will be held under the sponsorship of President Husni 
Mubarak on 4 May. The signing will be attended by U.S. 
Secretary of State Warren Christopher, Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev, and a representative of the Government of Norway 
which sponsored the secret negotiations, in addition to 
representatives from donor states. 
  Peres is expected to arrive in Cairo on Tuesday evening to 
follow up the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations closely, together 
with PLO Executive Committee. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

