<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian-Israeli Talks in Cairo Resume </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian-Israeli Talks in Cairo Resume </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2404150194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1420 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2404150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 24 Apr (MENA) -- Palestinian-Israeli talks to 
implement the agreement on self-rule in Gaza and Jericho resumed 
in Cairo this afternoon. The talks are chaired by Dr. Nabil 
Sha'th, political adviser to Palestinian president Yasir 
'Arafat, and General Amnon Shahaq, Israeli deputy chief of 
staff. The talks were scheduled to begin this morning but were 
delayed several hours because the Israeli delegation arrived in 
Cairo late. 
  Informed Palestinian sources told MENA that the current 
round 
takes on special importance because it will be the last round if 
the two sides agree on the outstanding issues. The sources said 
the most important issues that will be discussed in the context 
of the Security and Legal Affairs Committee is the legal 
jurisdiction in Gaza and Jericho and the release of Palestinian 
detainees in Israeli jails, estimated at approximately 10,000 
according to International Red Cross statistics. 

</TEXT>

