<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th, Shahaq Hold Closed Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th, Shahaq Hold Closed Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2404184194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1815 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2404184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 24 Apr (MENA)--Dr. Nabil Sha'th, adviser to 
Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat and head of the Palestinian 
delegation to the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations, today held a 
closed meeting with General Amnon Shahaq, Israeli deputy chief 
of staff. The meeting lasted for one and a half hours. 
  Knowledgeable Palestinian sources have stated that the talks 
dealt with the outcome of the previous rounds of talks. Sha'th 
and Shahaq reviewed the topics that will be discussed by the 
Security and Legal Affairs Committees during the current round 
of talks, the sources said. 
  The sources added that the Sha'th-Shahaq meeting aimed at 
eliminating any obstacles that might face the negotiations. The 
meeting also aimed at reaching a final agreement on implementing 
the Gaza-Jericho accord by the end of this week, the sources 
added. 

</TEXT>

