<H3> <TI>   More FRC Members Arrested for Diplomat's Assassination </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More FRC Members Arrested for Diplomat's Assassination </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2304103894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1015 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2304103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, 23 Apr (MENA)--Investigations by Lebanese 
judicial and security authorities with 16 members of the 
Abu-Nidal-led Fatah Movement--the Revolutionary Council [FRC] 
arrested a few days ago have revealed that eight of them were 
involved in the assassination a few months ago of Jordanian 
diplomat Na'ib al- Ma'aytah. The number of persons arrested in 
connection with the crime has thus risen to 11, after charges 
were pressed against three others. 
  The Lebanese Army troops on Thursday stormed one of the 
Abu-Nidal group's barracks in al-Rawdah, Western al-Biqa', and 
seized a large amount of weapons, ammunition, vehicles, and 
missiles estimated at 25 truck loads. The army arrested 16 FRC 
members. 

</TEXT>

