<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A large roadside charge exploded near an IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] force moving in the eastern sector of 
the security zone at midday. There were no casualties and no 
damage was caused. 
  Our correspondent Nati Zilberman reports that the IDF and 
SLA 
[South Lebanese Army] have been sporadically exchanging fire 
with Hizballah in recent hours. This morning, terrorists fired 
several mortar shells at SLA positions and at an IDF patrol near 
al-Rayhan. Our correspondent notes that today's exchanges of 
fire occurred after two days of quiet in the security zone. 

</TEXT>

