<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli Shelling, Resistance Attacks in South Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Shelling, Resistance Attacks in South Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Amal Attacks Reported </H4>

<F P=102> NC2304200194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1900 GMT 23 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2304200194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A NATIONAL NEWS AGENCY correspondent in al-Nabatiyah 
reports that the Iqlim al-Tuffah heights came under concentrated 
artillery fire from the occupation forces' positions at about 
1930 today. The shelling, which was accompanied by heavy 
machine-gun fire, was directed mainly at Mlita, al-Luwayzah, and 
Jabal Safi. At 2000 the forests of al-Litani were raked by 
bursts of machine-gun fire from positions held by the Agent Lahd 
militia [South Lebanese Army] in 'Alman and al-Shumariyah. 
  The occupation forces this afternoon shelled Qabrikha and 
Tulin with mortars and tank guns, causing heavy material damage. 
The Qabrikha-Majdal Silm road also came under sniper fire from 
the occupation forces' positions in Tallusi. 
  Meanwhile, the Amal Movement has announced that one of its 
groups attacked an enemy mechanized patrol on the 
al-Qantarah-al-Tayyibah road at 1745 today, using rockets and 
automatic weapons. An enemy M-113 armored personnel carrier was 
destroyed and all its occupants were killed or wounded. At the 
same time, another group attacked an infantry patrol on the same 
road, skirmishing with it for 15 minutes and killing or wounding 
some of its members. A third group directed concentrated 82-mm 
mortar fire against al-Qantarah. 

</TEXT>

