<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Bahrain </F>
<H3> <TI>   Egypt's President Arrives for 1-Day Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Egypt's President Arrives for 1-Day Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2404123694 Manama WAKH in Arabic 1100 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2404123694 </F>
<F P=104>  Manama WAKH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Manama, 24 Apr (WAKH) -- Egyptian President Husni 
Mubarak arrived in Manama from Abu Dhabi at noon today on a 
one-day official visit to Bahrain at the invitation of His 
Highness Shaykh 'Isa Bin- Salman Al Khalifah, the amir of 
Bahrain. 
  He was received at the airport by His Highness Shaykh 'Isa 
Bin- Salman Al Khalifah, the amir of Bahrain; His Highness 
Shaykh Khalifah Bin-Salman Al Khalifah, the prime minister; and 
His Highness Shaykh Hamad Bin-'Isa Al Khalifah, the heir 
apparent and commander in chief of the Bahraini Defense Force. 
The chief of the Amiri Court, the chairman of the Shura 
Council, ambassadors, and senior officials were also present at 
the reception ceremony. 
  The Egyptian president will hold talks on bilateral 
relations 
and ways to promote them in various domains. Talks will also 
deal with the latest Gulf, Arab, and international developments, 
particularly the Middle East peace process and issues of common 
concern. 
  Mubarak's delegation includes Egyptian Foreign Minister 'Amr 
Musa and Minister of Information Safwat al-Sharif. It also 
includes 'Atif 'Ubayd, minister of public business sector and 
minister of state for administrative development; the Chief of 
the President's Office Zakariya 'Azmi; a number of Egyptian 
Government officials, and a press and media delegation. 

</TEXT>

