<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Attack Repelled in Faryab Province </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Attack Repelled in Faryab Province </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304180194 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304180194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An attack by Dostam's militia was pushed back in 
(Garzedana) district, Faryab Province. A report from 'Abdol 
Karim Arshud, a courageous mojahedin commander, says that this 
morning at 0500 the Dostam militia launched a broad attack 
against mojahedin positions but the enemy were forced to 
retreat, leaving 24 dead. 
  The report adds that sixteen militiamen were captured alive 
by the mojahedin. One combat machine [as heard] and 16 
personnel carriers belonging to the enemy were destroyed. The 
report adds that six militiamen's corpses are still lying on the 
battlefield. During the fighting, over 20 heroic mojahedin 
received light injuries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

