<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fatah, Hamas Reach Cease-Fire Agreement in Gaza </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah, Hamas Reach Cease-Fire Agreement in Gaza </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Leaflet on Agreement Distributed </H4>

<F P=102> TA2204140894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 22 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2204140894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A one month-long cease-fire agreement between the 
Fatah Hawks and 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam, Hamas' [Islamic 
Resistance Movement] military arm, has been reached in the Gaza 
Strip. Our correspondent Nisim Qeynan reports that a leaflet to 
this effect was disseminated in the Gaza Strip today. It states 
that the two sides will halt acts of revenge against 
collaborators in order to enable them to dissociate themselves 
from their support of Israel. The two groups will also put an 
end to mutual acts of hostility and what they term unnecessary 
strikes. It was also decided to set up a committee to 
adjudicate conflicts between the sides during this cease-fire 
period. 
  Our correspondent notes that Fatah leaders in the Strip have 
not reacted to the agreement, but a Palestinian source says it 
was reached with the knowledge of senior leaders in both 
organizations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

