<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Meets, Notes Arab-European Dialogue, Blockade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly Meets, Notes Arab-European Dialogue, Blockade </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2404173194 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1530 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2404173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 24 Apr (INA) -- The National Assembly held 
a session today under the chairmanship of Deputy Speaker Ghanim 
'Aziz Khadduri. 
  At the beginning of the session, the people's 
representatives 
discussed a report, which the Assembly presented to the annual 
conference of the Arab-European parliamentary dialogue held in 
Paris from 14 to 17 April. Sixteen Arab parliaments and 13 
European parliaments, as well as representatives of the European 
Parliament, the Arab League, and the European Union also 
attended. 
  Assembly members Bashir Hammud al-Ghazali and 'Abd-al-Karim 
Jihad who participated in the conference said that participants 
stressed the need to implement Security Council resolutions 
calling for the achievement of a comprehensive and just peace in 
the region. 
  Regarding the imperialist-Zionist conspiracy that is 
targeting Iraq, they said that participants also acknowledged 
the suffering of the Iraqi people as a result of the continued 
unjust blockade. They also expressed their hope that the 
implementation of Security Council resolutions would lead to the 
lifting of the blockade. 
  The assembly then elected a permanent committee for 
environment. 'Abd-al-Karim Jihad was elected as chairman of the 
committee, Raja' al-Shawi as deputy chairman, and 'Abd-al-Majid 
Khunayjir as rapporteur. 

</TEXT>

