<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Clarification From Kurdistan </F>
Democratic Party: No Barzani Conditions for Visiting Damascus"] 
  [Excerpt] London, AL-HAYAH -- The Kurdistan Democratic 
Party [KDP] has hailed the "strong" relations between its leader 
Mas'ud Barzani and Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad. 
  AL-HAYAH has received a clarification from the party in 
Salah-al-Din in northern Iraq, which said: 
  "In your 20 April 1994 edition, you published a report under 
the headline "Barzani Sets Three Conditions for Acceptance of 
Damascus Invitation." In the interest of the truth, we wish to 
make the following clarification: 
  "1. Our party's relations with Syria are strong and based on 
mutual respect and understanding, and we attach much importance 
to these relations. 
  "2. President Hafiz al-Asad received Barzani on all his 
previous visits. Barzani's relations with President al-Asad are 
strong and warm. 
  "3. We wish to point out that Barzani would never visit 
Syria on preconditions. Syria is his own country and the gates 
of Damascus were and are still open. There is no need for 
preconditons between brothers." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

