<H4>    Delegation Visits Fishery Facilities </H4>

<F P=102> LD2404211394 Tehran IRNA in English 2042 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404211394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bandar Anzali (Gilan), April 24, (IRNA) -- The Irish 
minister of defence and marine affairs, David Andrews, and his 
delegation visited the fishery facilities at this Iranian port 
on the Caspian Sea. 
  The visit by the Irish official has been made upon the 
invitation of the Ministry of Construction Jihad. 
  The Iranian and Irish delegations exchanged views on fishing 
and related activities and cooperation. 
  After meeting with governor general of Gilan, Ali Akbar 
Tahaei, the Irish official visited Martyr Beheshti fish 
culturing workshops, Langar Dam, and Zibakenar which is a spot 
for fishing caviar. 

</TEXT>

