<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Irish Defense Minister Holds Talks With Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    President Receives Irish Minister </H4>

<F P=102> LD2504110194 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2504110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Hashemi-Rafsanjani today received David 
Andrews, Irish minister for defense and marine. In this 
meeting, the Irish minister for defense and marine conveyed the 
respects of his country's president and prime minister to the 
Iranian Government and people. He reported good progress in his 
talks with officials of the Ministry of Construction Jihad on 
the expansion of economic and trade relations between the two 
countries. He called for the signing of a memorandum of 
understanding between the two countries on the practical 
expansion of cooperation between Iran and Ireland. 
  In turn, Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani welcomed the expansion of 
relations with Ireland, and he expressed the hope that greater 
exchanges of political and economic delegations between the two 
countries will lead to an increase in future cooperation. 

</TEXT>

