<H3> <TI>   Turkmen Vice President Arrives, Welcomed by Velayati </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkmen Vice President Arrives, Welcomed by Velayati </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504100694 Tehran IRNA in English 0944 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2504100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 25, IRNA -- Turkmen Vice-President 
Boris Shikhmuradov arrived here this morning and was welcomed by 
Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati. He is carrying a message 
from Turkmen President Saparmurad Niyazov for his Iranian 
counterpart Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani. 
  Upon arrival at Mehrabad Airport, Shikhmuradov told IRNA 
that 
the objective of his trip was to discuss different issues, 
including matters of mutual interest, with high-ranking Iranian 
officials. He added that following the visit of the two 
presidents, mutual ties have been expanded and fundamental 
political and economic changes have been made in bilateral 
relations. 
  Shikhmuradov noted that another objective of his visit here 
was to make preparations for Niyazov's forthcoming visit to Iran. 
  Meanwhile, the Turkmen official and Velayati discussed the 
passing of Turkmenistan's gas pipelines to Europe through Iran. 
The two sides also studied implementation of agreements reached 
between the two countries during Niyazov's last trip to Iran. 

</TEXT>

