<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Received by Hashemi-Rafsanjani </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Received by Hashemi-Rafsanjani </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504104894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2504104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkmenistan's Vice President Shikhmuradov, who 
arrived in Tehran today, was received by President 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani and presented the latter with a written 
message from Turkmenistan's President Mr. Niyazov. 
  In the meeting, the president expressed satisfaction over 
the 
rate of expansion in friendly relations between Iran and 
Turkmenistan. He said the connection of the two countries' 
railways is of great significance for the increase of trade and 
economic exchanges as well as cargo transit between the 
countries of the European region and China. 
  Referring to plans to build a pipeline for the transfer of 
Turkmenistan's gas to Turkey through Iran, Mr. 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani announced that the Islamic Republic of Iran 
is ready to participate in the speedy implementation of the plan. 
  According to the Central News Unit, for his part the 
Turkmenistan vice president reported on the agreements reached 
between the two countries and called for the ever increasing 
expansion of bilateral relations on the regional and 
international levels and cooperation in the field of gas 
transfer. 
  Referring to the Afghanistan problem, he expressed support 
for Iran's humanitarian policy in solving the existing 
difficulties in that country. 

</TEXT>

