<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rowhani on Volunteers for Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rowhani on Volunteers for Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604095094 Tehran IRNA in English 0928 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2604095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 26, IRNA -- Majlis Vice-Speaker Hojjat 
ol-Eslam Hasan Rowhani said here Monday [25 April] that 10,000 
Iranian volunteer forces are presently awaiting the U.N. 
approval for being dispatched to Bosnia-Herzegovina. Speaking 
at the two-day seminar on policies of the world arrogance in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and other Islamic states, he remarked that 
despite Iran's readiness, the Iranian forces had not yet been 
allowed to be dispatched to that region. 
  The vice-speaker said that the west was using Russia as an 
excuse to withhold help to Muslims adding that the west was now 
pretending that it was Russia which, as a member of the Security 
Council, would veto decisions of other members made in favor of 
the Muslims. 
  He further said that if the U.S., Britain and France had not 
shown the green light to Russia, the latter would not have been 
in a position to stand against western powers. 
  Stressing that over 200,000 Bosnian Muslims were ready to 
struggle and sacrifice their lives, Rowhani concluded by saying 
that although the U.N. has confirmed that Bosnian Muslims are 
under Serbian aggressions, it has so far failed to provide them 
with defensive means. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

