<H3> <TI>   Red Crescent Chairman Comments on Aid to Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Red Crescent Chairman Comments on Aid to Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404103394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2404103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Islamic Republic of Iran's [IRI] Red 
Crescent Society will soon dispatch relief aid comprising 
foodstuff, clothing and other requirements to Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  The chairman of the IRI's Red Crescent Society, Mr. 
Seifollah 
Vahid Dastjerdi, today participated in an exclusive interview 
with our correspondent announcing the readiness of the society 
to collect donations for Muslims of Bosnia-Herzegovina. [passage 
omitted] 
  The chairman of the Red Crescent Society rounded up relief 
aid dispatched by the Red Crescent to Bosnia and said: 
  [Begin recording] [Dastjerdi] We have so far sent around 500 
tonnes of foodstuff. We gave more than $100,000 in cash to 
their welfare organization and other people who work in that 
respect. The society also bought around 500 million rials worth 
of clothing and distributed them at camps set up around Sarajevo 
and other places in Bosnia. 
  [Correspondent] The Red Crescent has also treated Bosnian 
Muslims, what can you tell us on that? 
  [Dastjerdi] I should mention that we have not carried out 
any 
treatment on the spot. We received some patients and 
handicapped persons from there. They were treated by the Red 
Crescent [in Iran]. [passage omitted] We again announce our 
preparedness to receive patients and particularly handicapped. 
  [Correspondent] Thank you very much. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

