<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   IRGC Issues Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IRGC Issues Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404165594 Tehran IRNA in English 1639 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 24, (IRNA) -- Islamic Revolution 
Guards Corps (IRGC) issuing a statement here today on the eve of 
the 14th anniversary of the aborted U.S. military offensive, 
recalling the memorable failure of American technology at Tabas, 
as "divine assistance". 
  The IRGC denouncing Washington's domineering policies, said 
the operation planned with "savage" precision and carried on 25 
April 1980, miserably floundered in the deserts around Tabas 
(over 600 kms southeast of Tehran) in Khorasan Province, burning 
beyond recognition the aggressors and their aircraft. 
  It was a miracle for which Iran will always remain thankful 
to the almighty. 
  The statement also condemned Washington's tacit support for 
Serb aggressors and their unabated "brutal" attacks on the 
defenceless Bosnian Muslims. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
